OL,3,CThe Metropolitan Police will resume
OL,4,Carresting Palestine Action protestors
OL,6,FEarlier this month Chief Magistrate
OL,7,FPaul Goldspring said the cases would
OL,8,Fbe delayed until after the High Court
OL,9,FAppeal over the ban is heard.
OL,11,FProscription makes it a criminal
OL,12,Foffence to belong to or support
OL,13,FPalestine Action, punishable by up to
OL,14,F14 years in prison.
OL,16,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,17,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,18,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,19,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,20,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,21,Fbelow...
